<page build="8099">
    <shortlink>ux loginwithgooglesettings</shortlink>
    <topic>Google settings</topic>
    <description>Settings to configure Google Authentication to add "Login with Google" functionality to an application using Integrated Login.</description>
    <discussion>
        <p>If the UX Component is configured to [Allow login with Google], the *[ui:Google settings]* property is available. This setting is used to configure the credentials for using Google Authentication to log into your application.</p>
    </discussion>
    <sections>
        <section>
            <figure>
                <title>Login with Google Settings</title>
                <alt>Login with Google Settings</alt>
                <link>images/logingooglesettings.png</link>
            </figure>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Google login Properties</title>
            <cases>
                <case>
                    <title nested="2">Client-id</title>
                    <description>
                        <p>The Google OAuth Client Id. See [Configure Login with Google] to learn how to create one.</p>
                    </description>
                </case>
                <case>
                    <title nested="2">Secret</title>
                    <description>
                        <p>The Google OAuth Secret. See [Configure Login with Google] to learn how to create one.</p>
                    </description>
                </case>
                <case>
                    <title nested="2">Policy</title>
                    <description>
                        <p>The *[ui:Policy]* defines the behavior when a user logs into your application using Google and does not have an existing account.</p>
                        <p>
                            <list>
                                <item>
                                    <name-title>Policy</name-title>
                                    <description-title>Description</description-title>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <name>CreateAccount</name>
                                    <description>If the user does not have an existing account, a new account is created.</description>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <name>DenyLogin</name>
                                    <description>If the user does not have an existing account, the login fails.</description>
                                </item>
                            </list>
                        </p>
                    </description>
                </case>
                <case>
                    <title nested="2">Groups</title>
                    <description>
                        <p>If the *[ui:Policy]* is configured to "CreateAccount", *[ui:Groups]* defines what groups (i.e. roles) assigned to the new user account.</p>
                    </description>
                </case>
            </cases>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>Videos</title>
        </section>
        <section>
            <videos>
                <title>Login using Google</title>
                <description>
                    <p>When you configure a UX component as a Login Component, you can enable Login with Google to allow users to login using the Google credentials.</p>
                </description>
                <date>2022-03-20</date>
                <video>
                    <name>Watch Video</name>
                    <link>https://youtu.be/IK1pIytPch0</link>
                </video>
            </videos>
        </section>
    </sections>
